    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Unique numeric identifiers used to create machine-readable codes for items, usually represented as barcodes. The identifiers were developed in the 1980s and originally called the "European Article Number"; the initials "EAN" were retained even though the term has been changed to "International Article Number."</Note_Text>
